An '''Iridium Bar''' is crafted by smelting 5 {{name|Iridium Ore|class=inline}} and 1 {{name|Coal|class=inline}} in a [[Furnace]]. Purple Slimes in the [[Skull Cavern]] or [[Slime Hutch]] have a chance to drop Iridium Bars and [[Iridium Ore|Ore]] when slain.  [[Shadow Shaman]] and [[Shadow Brute]]s can also drop an Iridium Bar when slain (0.2% chance). [[Bats|Iridium Bats]] may drop one as well (0.8% chance).  The [[Traveling Cart]] may sell an Iridium Bar for {{tprice|1000}}.  One Iridium Bar can also be received as a gift from [[Clint]] at the [[Feast of the Winter Star]].  Two to three Iridium Bars may occasionally be found in [[Skull Cavern#Treasure Rooms|treasure rooms]] in the Skull Cavern. The [[Statue Of Endless Fortune]] has a 25% chance to produce one daily, if it is not a villager's birthday.

An Iridium Bar can be [[Shipping|shipped]] or sold to [[Clint]] at the [[Blacksmith]] Shop for {{price|1000}}, or {{price|1500}} with the [[Skills#Mining|Blacksmith Profession]].

The [[Desert Trader]] in [[The Desert|the Calico Desert]] will trade one [[Warp Totem: Desert]] Recipe for 10 Iridium Bars.

==Tool Upgrades==
Iridium Bars are required for the final upgrade of tools.

